name: Bad Faith
description: When a deep state of anxiety occurs, tons of questions appear. If authenticity is a breath of existence, then how it should be achieved? Is it by rejecting the old values and do what we've desired to, or drown ourselves in the crowd? But in the end, the reality isn't always contrasted as the earth and the sky; the rejected ways aren't always bad, and overcome the crowd isn't always a good choice.
